<tr><td bgcolor="#3F403F" width="98%" class="cheader"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></td><td bgcolor="3F403F" valign="top" align="right" width="22"><img src="/swtcg/gfx/theme1/topcorner.gif" width="23" height="22" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0" align="right"></td></tr>
<tr><td width="98%" colspan=2><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" class="cbody">
<tr><td><font class="h1font"> How to Stall the Ground Arena for the Dark Side<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/swtcg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/swtcg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/swtcg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/swtcg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.25)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/swtcg/main/mpage.php?member=15'>Michael "Dvader" Girard</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/swtcg/main/mpage.php?member=15&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> May 9, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> First we&#39;ll go over some definitions, explanations, and a disclaimer.  First, the disclaimer, this strategy is something that I have been working on for the past couple weeks.  I feel that the best two arenas to effeciently win in are the character and space arenas.  The Ground Arena is the second of the three arenas in which you are competing for control.  <br>
<br>
The Ground Arena has a couple units that can be used for utility purposes as opposed to battle purposes.  The Jawa Sandcrawler, in my opinion, is the best cost/reward unit in the game.  It only costs four.  And for that four build, you get a unit that has mediocre power (yet still more powerful then the Coruscant Fighter).  More importantly, you get a 7 toughness for it.  That will mostly likely last at least two turns.  Any unit lasting longer then two turns has more then paid for it&#39;s build cost.  The ability &quot;T: Draw two cards, discard two cards&quot; is one that completes this units effectiveness.  The ability to quickly cycle through your deck is one that is highly sought after in ccg&#39;s that don&#39;t have a high draw count (Magic:TG for example).  This is beneficial because you are actually seeing more cards in your deck then your opponent, so eventually you will hit that card that you need at the right time.<br>
<br>
Another ground unit that is helpful for stalling out this specific arena is the Trade Federation Battleship Core.  Not only does this unit have a 12 health, but it&#39;s 10 power can also inflict some serious damage.  Now granted, the 9 build cost is quite steep, but I think that it&#39;s more then worth it, especially if you are able to build one of these bad boys during the Setup phase.<br>
<br>
A good cheap unit that may not stick around for long, but has an unmatched ability is Tyranus&#39;s Geonosian Speeder.  This unit only has a 2 power and 1 health, but the ability to go and get a battle card every turn offsets the poor stats.  This is probably the second most pivotal card in the process of stalling out the ground arena.  Each turn you can go and get a Peace on Naboo to prevent the damage that would be inflicted by the Light Sides millions of Clone troopers.  Not only that but you can go and get that one time Tyranus&#39;s Wrath, for when you absolutely, positively have to kill a light side house (Naboo Defense system).<br>
<br>
The rest of the units are up to you.  The Destroyer Droid Squad is very reasonable cost with decent stats.  The Commerce Guild Droid Platoon is good for helping to finish off the Space Arena (but don&#39;t forget, it doesn&#39;t work with Peace on Naboo).<br>
<br>
The card you need to use the most to perfect the stalling out is, of course, Peace on Naboo.  This will give your units a free turn to use their utility abilities and not have to worry about getting pounded by clone trooper squads or jedi squads.  Pilot&#39;s Dodge is another good battle card that will come in handy when needing to save a ground unit or three from the onslaught.<br>
<br>
This is what the final version is for stalling out the Ground Arena.<br>
<br>
Ground<br>
2x Trade Federation Battleship Core<br>
4x Jawa Sandcrawler<br>
2x Tyranus&#39;s Geonosian Speeder<br>
1x Commerce Guild Droid Platoon<br>
3x Destroyer Droid Squad<br>
<br>
Mission<br>
4x Peace on Naboo<br>
2x Pilot&#39;s Dodge<br>
1x Tyranus&#39;s Wrath<br>
<br>
I chose the Destroyer Droid Squad because, after all, you only have 4x Peace on Naboo and if you haven&#39;t clobbered the opponent in the other two arenas, then you are going to need to put up a fight.  <br>
<br>
There you have it, a nearly fool proof (sans bad dice or unit screwage during setup) way to stall out the Ground Arena while you take care of the other two.<br>
<br>
If you have any questions, drop me an email at dvader20@yahoo.com<br>
<br>
Michael Girard<br>
